Award-winning RnB group Boyz II Men have confirmed their South African tour dates after having to cancel twice during the Covid-19 lockdown in 2020 and 2021. The concerts will take place in Cape town on 31 October at the Grand Arena, GrandWest, in Pretoria at the SunBet Arena, Time Square on Thursday, 2 November and in the North West at the Superbowl in Sun City on Saturday,  4 November. 
 
G21 Entertainment frontman Glen Netshipise said they were elated to finally kick off the tour in South Africa later this year. “Boyz II Men promised their fans a killer live show shortly before the pandemic, and now keeping true to that promise, now that it’s safe to do so. With three shows planned around the country, we look forward to delivering yet another quality production with this multiple award-winning music outfit,” said Netshipise. For the latest entertainment news from Sunday World, click here. Or read the latest from Shwashwi here. Follow @SundayWorldZA on Twitter and @sundayworldza on Instagram, or like our Facebook Page, Sunday World, by clicking here for the latest breaking news in South Africa. To Subscribe to Sunday World, click here